---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { bySlug, REPO_URL } from '../lib/registry';

const reading = [
  {
    doc: bySlug('convictions'),
    time: '5 min',
    why: 'The truths this rests on, stated plainly — a good first read to see whether the premise holds up.',
  },
  {
    doc: bySlug('covenant'),
    time: '5 min',
    why: 'The actual commitments: eight of them, specific, signed by a household and renewed each year.',
  },
  {
    doc: bySlug('protocol'),
    time: '15 min',
    why: 'How the hard conversation between two families is meant to go, scripts included — the piece that makes the standard enforceable rather than aspirational.',
  },
  {
    doc: bySlug('plan'),
    time: '30–45 min · optional',
    why: 'The full case: the drift being named, the theology behind it, the six pillars, and the year-one pilot.',
  },
];
---

<Base
  title="For Parents"
  description="The Golden Rule, restored as the standard — why culture drifts without one, and the playbook for parents who want to hold it on purpose."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-20 pb-14 text-center">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-6">For Parents</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-5xl sm:text-6xl font-semibold leading-[1.08] text-ink-deep text-balance">
      The Golden Rule, restored as the standard
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-7 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-soft max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Not a slogan on a classroom wall, but the plain, enforced expectation of daily life — the standard a grade's families hold together, on purpose. This is the parent playbook: why culture drifts without one, and where to begin.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Why -->
  <section class="border-y border-line bg-paper-deep">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-14 text-center">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Why this exists</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-semibold text-ink-deep mb-6">Culture doesn’t hold itself together</h2>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
        Left alone, a school culture drifts toward whatever its most persistent voices normalize — one grade, one group chat, one birthday-party guest list at a time. Kindness becomes something to praise when it shows up, rather than something to expect. None of this is anyone's fault in particular; it's simply what happens when a culture is left undirected instead of built on purpose.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The standard -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16 text-center">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-4">The standard, not the goal</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-semibold text-ink-deep mb-6">Kindness and dignity are the floor</h2>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
      The Golden Rule set the bar a long time ago. The Savio Standard treats it as a floor a grade's families can name, expect, and hold together — not an aspiration to hope for, and not a weight any one family should carry alone.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- The antidote -->
  <section class="border-y border-line bg-paper-deep">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-14 text-center">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-4">The antidote</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-semibold text-ink-deep mb-6">A playbook, not a program</h2>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
        This project exists so no parent has to build the response from scratch: a covenant already written, a shared language already tested, a protocol for the hard conversation already scripted, and a community structure — School Leads, Homeroom Hosts — already designed. Four documents cover the essentials.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reading order -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16">
    <div class="ornament mb-10"><span class="eyebrow">Read these, in this order</span></div>
    <ol class="space-y-8">
      {
        reading.map((r, i) => (
          <li class="flex gap-5">
            <div class="font-display text-3xl text-gold font-semibold shrink-0 w-8 text-center">{i + 1}</div>
            <div>
              <a
                href={'/' + r.doc!.slug}
                class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-ink-deep hover:text-gold transition-colors"
              >
                {r.doc!.title}
              </a>
              <span class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-ink-soft/70 ml-2">{r.time}</span>
              <p class="font-sans text-[0.95rem] leading-relaxed text-ink-soft mt-1.5">{r.why}</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- How it starts -->
  <section class="border-y border-line bg-paper-deep">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16 text-center">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-4">How it starts</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-semibold text-ink-deep mb-6">Quietly, or all at once</h2>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
        It can start small: a parent reads, signs the covenant privately, and mentions it to a couple of families already trusted in the grade. When eight households in a grade have signed, the grade activates and everyone is introduced at once — no family holds the standard by itself. Or it can move faster: a family ready to launch it school-wide becomes the <a href="/roles" class="text-gold underline underline-offset-2">Director</a> themselves, or finds the parent who should be, and builds the founding team directly rather than waiting for a grade to fill in on its own. Either way, it runs independent of the school and the parish, alongside them rather than through them.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4 font-sans">
        <a
          href="/covenant"
          class="rounded-md bg-ink-deep px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide text-paper uppercase hover:bg-ink transition-colors"
        >
          Read the Covenant
        </a>
        <a
          href="/library"
          class="rounded-md border border-gold px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide text-gold uppercase hover:bg-gold hover:text-paper transition-colors"
        >
          See everything else
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-8 font-sans text-sm text-ink-soft">
        Looking to bring this to a school's leadership instead? There's a <a href="/for-schools" class="text-gold underline underline-offset-2">starter page for that</a>, too.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 font-sans text-sm text-ink-soft">
        Questions, or want to be one of the founding families? Best way in is <a href={`${REPO_URL}/issues`} class="text-gold underline underline-offset-2">an issue on GitHub</a> — or reach a maintainer directly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
